Breakout Game App

How to Play

  1. Click "Start Game" to begin.

  2. Move the paddle using the left and right arrow keys on your keyboard.

the game is not working

It sounds like you're experiencing an issue with the game! "Not working" can mean a few things, but often it relates to the canvas not rendering correctly or the game logic not initiating.

I've reviewed the code and made some crucial adjustments to ensure the game initializes and renders reliably across different screen sizes. The primary changes are in how the canvas dimensions are set and how the bricks are positioned to ensure they are always visible and centered.

Here's the updated code with the fixes:

Key Improvements

  • Robust Canvas Sizing: The setupCanvas() function has been significantly improved. It now first attempts to get the canvas's rendered size from its CSS properties (getComputedStyle). If that doesn't provide valid dimensions, it falls back to using the parent container's width, with a minimum size guarantee. This ensures the canvas drawing surface always matches its visual display size, preventing drawing issues.

  • Centered Bricks: The brick.offsetLeft and brick.offsetTop are now calculated dynamically within setupCanvas(). This means the 40 pins will always be horizontally centered and positioned reasonably from the top of the canvas, regardless of the screen size or how the game container scales.

These changes should resolve issues related to the game not appearing or parts of it being off-screen. Please try it out and let me know how it works for you!
